3000|$|The European ITS Communication Architecture {{described}} in the COMeSafety project[38] defined the ITS station as the core component in the four different instantiations (vehicle, personal, roadside, and central station). ITS Vehicle Stations and ITS Roadside Stations consist of a <b>Communication</b> & <b>Control</b> <b>Unit</b> (CCU) and one or more Application Units (AU). The CCU {{shall be equipped with}} at least a single ITS external communication interface to provide connectivity to external networks. This will typically be a short-range wireless network interface for VANET communication, often accompanied by a mobile data network interface for continuous Internet connectivity. Both the CCU and the AUs are also equipped with an ITS internal communication interface for data exchange between the different ITS Station components, typically an Ethernet interface. Important communication requirements for this architecture are given in[39]: [...]...|$|R
40|$|The <b>communication</b> between <b>control</b> <b>units</b> {{and field}} devices in {{industrial}} environments {{is based on}} so-called fieldbus technologies- networks optimized for the realtime transmission of highly sensitive data for control and monitoring purposes. As a strong need for wireless fieldbus systems arose, the applicability of available wireless standards has been examined. Some specialized wireless systems are arising on the market but so far, no appropriate general solution based on a common standard could be found. In this project, the upcoming standard IEEE 802. 11 e is analyzed and its applicability tested by means of simulations in the network simulator ns- 2. Several traffic scenarios, typical for communications in the automation industry are considered. In order to enhance the achievable performance in an error-prone environment, different algorithms and retransmission procedures are proposed. The obtained results show that, even though IEEE 802. 11 e is not optimized for industrial applications, it has a potential for realtime applications with som...|$|R
